abstract: GE Capital said on Wednesday that it had agreed to sell mortgages worth about 5 billion Australian dollars to Pepper Homeloans for an undisclosed sum, as high prices feed concern about a bubble in Australia’s housing market.
snippet: GE Capital said on Wednesday that it had agreed to sell mortgages worth about 5 billion Australian dollars to Pepper Homeloans for an undisclosed sum, as high prices feed concern about a bubble in Australia’s housing market.
lead_paragraph: GE Capital said on Wednesday that it had agreed to sell mortgages worth about 5 billion Australian dollars ($5.2 billion) to Pepper Homeloans for an undisclosed sum, as high prices in the country’s housing market reinforce fears about its real estate sector.

headline.main: GE Capital Unloads $5.2 Billion in Australian Loans
